properties.description: The former studio home of the sculptor Dora Gordine and her husband the Hon. Richard Hare, a scholar of Russian art and literature. 1930s house over four floors including a flat roof terrace and views of Richmond Park.
properties.name: Dorich House Museum

properties.description: The current building, the third on the site, was built between 1927-1933 in the Art Deco style, as a memorial to the 3,225 Freemasons who died in World War I. It is a Grade II* listed building, both internally and externally.

images.title: View our fantastic Organ in the Grand Temple
The kids will love our Lego Lodge
You can learn more about Freemasonry in our dedicated museum
The stunning art deco style Temple Doors can be moved be opened with your little finger!
Children can make and take a dragon, throne or unicorn which all appear in the building
Freemasons' Hall was built as a Peace Memorial to more than 3,000 Freemasons who died in WW1

properties.name: Freemasons' Hall

properties.description: Grade I listed Georgian garden building. Tribute to Shakespeare built in the Ionic style by actor David Garrick. Arcadian Thames-side setting in restored 18C gardens thought to be by Capability Brown.

properties.description: A small, charming Gothic Revival cemetery chapel made from Kentish ragstone, with plate tracery and a mosaic alterpiece. It was deconsecrated and then restored for community use. Thomas Hardy was apprenticed to the architect.

images.title: View of the chapel from Grove Gardens

properties.name: Grove Gardens Chapel

properties.description: The City's seat of municipal government since 12C. Grade I listed, rare example of medieval civic architecture.
properties.name: Guildhall

properties.description: 17C livery hall with courtroom and garden. Oak panelling and stained glass windows. Undamaged in WWII. Recently refurbished new rooms and air-cooling within.  Selected items from the archives on display. Book binding exhibition in the Hall.

images.title: Caxton Window in the Main Hall

properties.name: Stationers' Hall

properties.description: Grade II* listed late Georgian elliptical 3-storey stuccoed villa.
properties.name: The Round House

properties.description: Classic Grade I listed Georgian church with outstanding interior and monuments. Renovated 2019/20.
properties.name: St Mary's Church, Battersea

properties.description: An enduring, distinctive feature of the London skyline for the last 54 years, this is a rare opportunity for members of the public to visit the famous revolving floor, 158m above the capital. After the flight the guests can watch a history of the BT Tower film in our auditorium.
properties.name: BT Tower

properties.description: Grade II listed building inspired by the ideals of John Ruskin and William Morris and contains Dickinson's paintings, hand-made furniture, furnishings, metalwork and friezes, in Arts & Crafts style. Reopening after a refurbishment project.

properties.description: Early 18C Grade II listed building incorporating plunge bath with Delft tiles, orangery, saloon and pump chamber with part-restored water wheel. Hermitage and sham bridge in grounds.
properties.name: Carshalton Water Tower and Historic Gardens

properties.description: Situated in one of the largest and grandest 19th century squares in London, 1 Belgrave Square was acquired by Romania in 1936 and is now home to the Romanian Cultural Institute.
properties.name: Romanian Cultural Institute

properties.description: The Air Raid Shelter was first built in 1939 for the the residents of St Leonards Court. A dormitory annex with 48 beds was added in 1940.  Some of the original features, such as handmade lampshades, are remarkably well preserved.

properties.description: St Anne's Limehouse has been described as 'the finest parish church in England.' Designed by Nicholas Hawksmoor, it is Grade I listed and one of the Major Churches in the Church of England. It is home to a thriving Christian congregation.
properties.name: St Anne's Church, Limehouse

properties.description: A monumental, inhabitable sculpture placed on a wing of the listed façade of The Beaumont Hotel. The interior, a bedroom, is as important as its exterior: a giant crouching cuboid figure based on the artist's body.
properties.name: ROOM by Antony Gormley

properties.description: A floating roof of sound, GPS-triggered & accessed by headphones & Echoes app to playfully reframe public space as an essential community engagement. One of 15 in an international series drawing on Oskar & Zofia Hansen’s Open Form concept.
